# Docs consistency guard (Cursor)

When editing any file matching the globs above (spec docs, root `idea.md`, or AGENTS.md), follow the
**FMD reconciliation and verification model** defined canonically in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

Do not restate the steps here — follow the version in AGENTS.md so there is only one copy. In
short: read `docs/index.md` §0 (one fact, one owner); keep every `F-###` and `INV-###` traced to
the QA plan; declare auth/authz on every network surface; and do not reintroduce Google Maps or
OpenRouteService as the map/routing stack. Current report data is Supabase-owned; Firebase Auth
and Firestore role records remain separate. See `docs/system-design.md` for details.
